I propose **Curvature-Adaptive Block-Level Routing**, a training-free precision routing framework that operationalizes spectral Hessian diagnostics to enable provably-stable mixed-precision inference without retraining or calibration loops.

**Key Innovation**: Block-level precision decisions are derived from deterministic spectral diagnostics of local Hessian conditioning, with formal stability radius bounds and PAC-Bayes generalization certificates. This bridges curvature geometry directly with routing logic, eliminating heuristic fragility.

